<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1094" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1094">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20229</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Antonio</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is my candid opinion that the withdrawal of the American troops from
                            Chihuahua would produce satisfactory results and would place the
                            responsibility for restoring order in Mexico on the <hi rend="italic">de
                                facto</hi> Government where it belongs. If <hi rend="italic">de
                                facto</hi> Government fails its weakness will soon be demonstrated
                            and all the world will understand. Our troops should all be kept near
                            the international border and in my opinion no more state troops should
                            now be mustered out as they are needed here and probably there may be
                            greater need a little later on.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>